Title: Label sentences as "important" or not
Description: In this HIT you have to read sentences that people spoke in a meeting, and label them as either important, neutral or unimportant.
Answer.comment: It was hard to determine what was neutral and what was unimportant sometimes.  Also, a person's sentence was often broken into several lines and was nonconsecutive since other people were also speaking so it made it hard to follow the conversation.
